{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778714843,"nonce":"INtGlEdlPJ4YJjrVcU2ZMeeF7qg=","title":".gitignore missing whitelist for results/**/figures/**/figure.html — symlinks silently skipped","message":".gitignore whitelists figure.json and figure.png but not figure.html. The render symlinks at results/\u003cexp\u003e/figures/\u003ctopic\u003e/figure.html (pointing to ../../../../_artifacts/\u003cexp\u003e/figures/\u003ctopic\u003e/figure.html) are silently excluded by git add, so they never stage, never merge, and never reach main.\n\nThe gap: !results/**/figures/**/figure.html is absent.\n\nWhy older symlinks survived: they were tracked before the ignore rules tightened; git does not re-evaluate already-tracked files against updated .gitignore patterns.\n\nWhy new symlinks vanish: silently skipped by git add at every stage — they look like untracked files that match the results/** catch-all, and since figure.html is not in the whitelist, they never get staged.\n\nThe fix: add !results/**/figures/**/figure.html to .gitignore, adjacent to the figure.png whitelist.\n\nRecovery: recreate the symlinks where renders exist in _artifacts/\u003cexp\u003e/figures/\u003ctopic\u003e/figure.html. Affected: b399efc (6 topics), 2bc95fd (training_loss + training_loss_per_term), 410d7ac (delta_v_signature). efc4d68/variance_profiles skipped — no render in _artifacts.\n\nCross-ref: 0f1af24 (closed; original symlink work), f485c26 (closed; results/ reorg + dual-tree convention).","files":null}]}